===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr}} [[bombarde]] bombard (as cannon), itself from {{etyl|el}} [[βαμβος]] (''bambos'') 'shattering'

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# a [[medieval]] primitive [[cannon]], used chiefly in [[siege]]s for throwing heavy stone balls.
# {{obsolete}} a [[bassoon]]-like medieval instrument

